race.comment: BRIEF STATEMENT (8) has missed the placings but in blanket finishes at her two runs this prep, both over 1000m at BM66 level. Tackles a better field today but looks in need of 1200m now and she gets some nice weight relief. Has won twice when third-up and can add to that record today. STRATIFIED (2) has battled on fairly for three midfield finishes since returning from a spell, all in open company. Won last prep in this grade carrying 1kg less. Very fit and ready to peak. ROUGE MOULIN (5) got going late to grab third in his latest appearance in open company over 1100m at Coonabarabran. Drops 3kgs after the claim and is back in a Benchmark race. Beautifully drawn so there is plenty of appeal. LAUREL HILL (3) hasn't won for a long while but is rarely far away. In the money at nine of 12 runs over today's journey. Must go in the exotics. LIFE'S A PARTY (7) returned to form last time out and at just the fourth run of the campaign can make further progress.
